                    "comment": "nealrichardson commented on issue #6517: ARROW-7984: [R] Check for valid inputs in more places \nURL: https://github.com/apache/arrow/pull/6517#issuecomment-594200765\n \n \n   @pitrou Sure, it's easy enough to add checks in the bindings, but are you sure this is something the C++ library should permit? Segfaults aside, it also looks like I can access memory outside of the Array if I slice with a negative index:\r\n   \r\n   ```r\r\n   > a <- Array$create(1:5)\r\n   > a\r\n   Array\r\n   <int32>\r\n   [\r\n     1,\r\n     2,\r\n     3,\r\n     4,\r\n     5\r\n   ]\r\n   > a$Slice(-10)\r\n   Array\r\n   <int32>\r\n   [\r\n     1409303264,\r\n     32691,\r\n     1427188520,\r\n     32691,\r\n     1415194568,\r\n     32691,\r\n     5,\r\n     0,\r\n     0,\r\n     0,\r\n     1,\r\n     2,\r\n     3,\r\n     4,\r\n     5\r\n   ]\r\n   ```\n \n----------------------------------------------------------------\nThis is an automated message from the Apache Git Service.\nTo respond to the message, please log on to GitHub and use the\nURL above to go to the specific comment.\n \nFor queries about this service, please contact Infrastructure at:\nusers@infra.apache.org\n",
